    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-28T16:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-28T16:15:00-05:00" n="394"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d394">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/1–2252: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 394<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation at the United Nations General
                            Assembly</gloss>, at Paris</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d394fn1">Repeated to Tel Aviv, London, Ankara, and
                        Cairo.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-28T16:15:00-05:00"
                            >January 28, 1952—4:15 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Gadel1">Gadel</gloss> 853. While US mindful of Israel as well
                    as world interests in free transit Suez Canal (<gloss target="#t_Delga1"
                        >Delga</gloss> 1142)<note n="2" xml:id="d394fn2">
                        <ref target="#d389">Document 389</ref>.</note> believe reopening question
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> res Sep 1 re Suez this time wld not serve
                    Israel’s best interests or those other interested parties or contribute to
                    settlement this problem. Present status Anglo-Egyptian relations make unlikely
                    any <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> action wld be effective or helpful this
                    time. Also believe public discussion of issues or attempt by Israel make test
                    case wld only exacerbate already seriously strained relations between Egypt and
                    West. When progress has been made in solution Anglo-Egyptian question more
                    opportune occasion may arise take up implementation <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                        >SC</gloss> res Sep 1.</p>
                <p>Recommend you inform <persName corresp="#p_EAS1">Eban</persName> US views and
                    suggest he may wish limit himself this time to informal talks with cosponsors
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> res Sep 1. Emb Tel Aviv auth inform <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> US views this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
